    <p>TOKYO • Ja­pan’s bad­minton world No. 1 Kento Mo­mota yes­ter­day an­nounced his long-awaited re­turn to com­pe­ti­tion as he be­gins his bid for home glory at the Tokyo Olympics nearly a year af­ter suf­fer­ing se­ri­ous in­juries in a car crash.</p>
    <p>The 26-year-old will com­pete at the All-Ja­pan na­tional cham­pi­onships in Tokyo later this month be­fore play­ing in the Thai­land Open next month. This fol­lows a dif­fi­cult year in which he feared his ca­reer might be over af­ter frac­tur­ing an eye socket in the ac­ci­dent in Jan­uary in Malaysia.</p>


